        "message": "LU-708 utils: refactor mkfs/tunefs/mount\n\nPort of ORI-294. Original patch locates at\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/1357\n\nRefactor the mkfs.lustre, tunefs.lustre, mount.lustre utilities\nto cleanly support multiple backend filesystems.  While this\ncommit initially appears large it does not introduce any\nfunctional changes.  It does however do the following.\n\n* Global variables consolidated in mkfs_opts/mount_opts\n  structures so this information may be cleanly passed to\n  common functions provided by mount_util.c.\n\n* Functions which were defined once in each utility have\n  been made common and consolidated in mount_utils.c.  In\n  a few cases the common function was made mode generic.\n\n* Split mkfs.lustre and tunefs.lustre in seperate .c files\n  for clarity.  This removes the need for the TUNEFS #define.\n\n* General cleanup.  This includes removing unused variables\n  and function, renaming functions for consistently, and\n  removing unused headers.\n\nThe bulk of this ldiskfs specific code was simply moved from the\nexisting utilties and consolidated in mount_utils_ldiskfs.c.\nMinimal changes were made to support the refactored infrastructure.\n\nA small fix was also made to the lustre spec file.  It was\nmistakenly checking if the libiam.c file exists and then assuming\nit was safe to add the libiam.a library.  However, the library\nwill only be build when the the ldiskfs osd code is enabled so\nit should check for the .a file.\n\nAuthor: Brian Behlendorf <behlendorf1@llnl.gov>\n\ntest-framework should not resolve the path to utils like mkfs.lustre\nand tunefs.lustre on a lustre client since client-only RPMs no longer\nhave those tools installed (check ORI-415 for more background).\n\nAuthor: Johann Lombardi <johann@whamcloud.com>\n\nSigned-off-by: Bobi Jam <bobijam@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ic98c18f3072cf4a3d6a17c10763f8a70ba6dc5c7\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
